OL,3,CFirst 'bionic peer' enters House of
OL,4,CLords, vowing to fight for sepsis
OL,5,Csurvivors
OL,7,FThe House of Lords' first ever
OL,8,F"bionic" peer has said he is
OL,9,Fdetermined to raise awareness of
OL,10,Fsepsis and has vowed to improve the
OL,11,Fquality of prosthetics offered to
OL,12,Ffellow amputees.
OL,14,FLord Mackinlay, of Richborough, is the
OL,15,Ffirst quadruple amputee to be
OL,16,Fintroduced to the House of Lords after
OL,17,Fhe was given a peerage in Rishi
OL,18,FSunak's dissolution honours list.
