OL,3,CFirst 'bionic peer' enters House of
OL,4,CLords, vowing to fight for sepsis
OL,5,Csurvivors
OL,7,FThe former Conservative MP for South
OL,8,FThanet, was rushed to hospital and put
OL,9,Fin a 16-day induced coma in September
OL,10,F2023. His wife was told he only had a
OL,11,F5% chance of survival.
OL,13,FThe 57-year-old then had both legs and
OL,14,Fboth arms amputated in December.
OL,16,FSpeaking on life after sepsis, he
OL,17,Fsaid: "You're reliant on other people,
OL,18,Fand you do get frustrated, and I've
OL,19,Fnever been the most patient of
OL,20,Fcharacters even before this. So yes,
OL,21,Fit's difficult.
